text:
Amsterdam Avenue, east side, south from W. 128th (intersection seen at left) to Lawrence (W. 126th) Streets, showing a cold storage plant of the Bernheimer and Schwartz Pilsener Brewing Company occupying this block front. Low buildings at the right are at the S.E. corner of Lawrence Street. To the left margin appears a portion of the Third Avenue Railway Co. barn.

March 1938.

P.L. Sperr

Street car barns, Amsterdam Avenue, east side, from 128th to 129th Streets.

June 14, 1931.

P. L. Sperr, Photographer.
